===Etymology===
From {{etyl|fro}} {{term|lymon||citrus|lang=fro}}, from {{etyl|ar}} {{term|ليمون|tr=laymūn|sc=Arab|lang=ar}} or {{etyl|ota}} {{term|sc=fa-Arab|لیمون|tr=limun}}, from {{etyl|fa}} {{term|لیمو|tr=limu|lang=fa}}. Cognate with {{etyl|sa|-}} {{term|निम्ब||lime|tr=nimbū|lang=sa}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/ˈlɛmən/|lang=en}}, {{X-SAMPA|/"lEm@n/|lang=en}}
* {{audio|En-uk-lemon.ogg|Audio (UK)}}
* {{rhymes|ɛmən|lang=en}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# A yellowish [[citrus]] [[fruit]].
# A semitropical [[evergreen]] [[tree]], ''[[Citrus limon]]'', that bears such fruits.
# A taste or [[flavour]]/[[flavor]] of lemons.
# A more or less bright [[shade]] of [[yellow]] associated with lemon fruits.
#: {{color panel|lemon flesh|2=FADA5E}}
#: {{color panel|lemon rind|2=FDE910}}
# {{slang}} A [[defective]] or [[inadequate]] item.
#: ''He didn’t realise until he’d paid for it that the car was a '''lemon'''.''
# {{context|Cockney rhyming|_|slang|from "lemon tart"}} [[smart|Smart]]; [[cheeky]], [[vocal]].
#*'''2009''', {{w|Caitlin Moran}}, ‘Why I love paying tax’, ''The Times'', 12 Oct 2009:
#*:Obviously Emin is not the first public figure to get '''lemon''' over tax increases.
# {{context|[[Cockney rhyming slang]]|shortened from “lemon flavour”}} [[favour]], [[favor]].
#: ''A thousand quid for that motor? Do me a '''lemon''', I could get it for half that.''
# {{fandom}} A piece of [[fanfiction]] involving [[explicit]] sex.

